From: Peters, C.J. <cjp0@cdc.gov>

West Nile Virus Transmission: Information on Pathogenesis?
----------------------------------------------------------
I would think that a simple pathogenesis study would be of considerable
importance in looking at these issues, if it has not already been done. The
usual "grind and find" plus clinical observations plus immunhistochemical
studies to identify the sites of replication would give a basis for
interpreting the epidemiological studies. Of course the experimenters would
give particular attention to throat swab, cloacal swab, feather follicles as
sources of infectious virus.
--
Peters, C.J.
<cjp0@cdc.gov>
