From: Henry Rupp <h.rupp@worldnet.att.net>

West Nile Virus Transmission: Ingestion?
-----------------------------------------
The ingestion of contaminated material (i.e. crows feeding on infected
nestlings of other species, the "bad oyster" theory) had been earlier
suggested as a route of entry for the virus in crows. Has any work been done
to determine what is a lethal oral dose of the virus? The entry of virus
into a bird's system by mechanical means is known in pheasant flocks, but is
stepping in "virally contaminated feces" (a real or supposed phenomenon?)
really analogous to the pecking that goes on in pheasant flocks?
--
Henry R. Rupp
<h.rupp@att.net>
